39,0,0,"Renewable energy resources have historically played a small role for electricity generation in the US. However, concerns such as security of energy supply, limitations and price fluctuations of fossil fuels, and threats of climate changes have encouraged US policy makers to think and debate about diversification strategy in the energy supply and promotion of renewables. The current paper discusses the role of renewable portfolio in the US energy action plan during 2010-2030. A system dynamics model is constructed to evaluate different costs of renewable energy utilization by 2030. Results show that while renewables will create a market with near 10 billion $ worth (in the costs level) in 2030, the total value of renewable energy promotion and utilization in the US will be more than 170 billion $(in the costs level) during 2010-2030. © 2013 Elsevier Ltd.","['renewable', 'energy', 'resources', 'played', 'small', 'role', 'electricity', 'generation', 'concerns', 'security', 'energy', 'supply', 'limitations', 'price', 'fluctuations', 'fossil', 'fuels', 'threats', 'climate', 'changes', 'encouraged', 'policy', 'makers', 'debate', 'diversification', 'strategy', 'energy', 'supply', 'promotion', 'renewables', 'current', 'discusses', 'role', 'renewable', 'portfolio', 'energy', 'action', 'plan', 'system', 'dynamics', 'model', 'constructed', 'evaluate', 'different', 'costs', 'renewable', 'energy', 'utilization', 'results', 'show', 'renewables', 'create', 'market', 'worth', 'costs', 'level', 'total', 'value', 'renewable', 'energy', 'promotion', 'utilization', 'costs', 'level', 'elsevier_ltd']"
40,0,0,"In order to implement sustainable economic policies, realistic and high accuracy demand projections are key to drawing and implementing realizable environmentally-friendly energy policies. However, some core energy models projections depict considerably high forecast inaccuracies in their previous projections. The inaccuracies are due to the massive assumption-driven variables whose assumptions and scenarios typically deviate from their realized levels. Here, we propose a high-accuracy assumption-free own-data-driven technique that utilizes zero of the traditional determinants as well as assumptions or scenarios for sectorial energy demand forecasting; and implement it in the United States (U.S.). The results show that the forecast accuracy of our gated recurrent network presents an enormous improvement on Annual Energy Outlook 2008 forecast projections. With evidence that our proposed sequential algorithm outperformed Annual Energy Outlook 2008 forecast projections, our proposed algorithm will guide policymakers in making sustainable energy-related policies in the near future. Although future realized consumption levels are unknown, we present our estimated projections along with Annual Energy Outlook 2018 projections to inform policymakers on future energy demands for the commercial sector, industrial sector, residential sector, and transportation. © 2018 by the authors.","['order', 'implement', 'sustainable', 'economic', 'policies', 'realistic', 'high', 'accuracy', 'demand', 'projections', 'key', 'drawing', 'implementing', 'realizable', 'energy', 'policies', 'core', 'energy', 'models', 'projections', 'depict', 'high', 'forecast', 'inaccuracies', 'previous', 'projections', 'inaccuracies', 'due', 'massive', 'assumption', 'driven', 'variables', 'assumptions', 'scenarios', 'deviate', 'realized', 'levels', 'propose', 'high', 'accuracy', 'assumption', 'free', 'data', 'driven', 'technique', 'utilizes', 'zero', 'traditional', 'determinants', 'assumptions', 'scena